<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="344" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1725,2002]" pageId="1" pageNumber="344">
<emphasis box="[199,297,1833,1857]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="344">Remarks</emphasis>
. Gude (
<number box="[398,455,1833,1857]" pageId="1" pageNumber="344" value="1911.0">1911</number>
) proposed 
<taxonomicName box="[591,691,1834,1857]" class="Gastropoda" family="Oxychilidae" genus="Drouetia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="1" pageNumber="344" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[591,691,1834,1857]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="344">Drouetia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a monotypic genus for the endemic 
<taxonomicName box="[1175,1347,1833,1857]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicidae" genus="Helix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="1" pageNumber="344" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="atlantica">
<emphasis box="[1175,1347,1833,1857]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="344">Helix atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which according to Morelet (
<number box="[401,460,1869,1893]" pageId="1" pageNumber="344" value="1860.0">1860</number>
) occurred in most islands of the Azores. Zilch (
<number box="[994,1052,1869,1893]" pageId="1" pageNumber="344" value="1959.0">1959</number>
) relegated the name to subgeneric status, and since then it has been generally accepted in this category. After Riedel’s (
<number box="[1128,1186,1905,1929]" pageId="1" pageNumber="344" value="1964.0">1964</number>
) anatomical research, several new species of 
<taxonomicName box="[421,521,1943,1966]" class="Gastropoda" family="Oxychilidae" genus="Drouetia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="1" pageNumber="344" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[421,521,1943,1966]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="344">Drouetia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been recognized (Martins 
<number box="[896,1026,1941,1965]" pageId="1" pageNumber="344" value="1981.1989">1981, 1989</number>
) and the group was recorded in all Azorean islands (Martins 
<emphasis box="[440,497,1977,2001]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="344">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[504,634,1977,2001]" pageId="1" pageNumber="344" value="1989.199">1989, 1990</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
